gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Hawks 127, 76ers 121
gameRecap.excerpt: Trae Young led the Hawks with 37 points, 12 assists, and five 3PT FGs as the Hawks defeated the 76ers, 127-121. Onyeka Okongwu added 21 points and eight rebounds while Jalen Johnson totaled 11 points, 11 rebounds, and six assists. Kelly Oubre Jr. (28 points, 12 rebounds) and Tobias Harris (21 points, six rebounds, seven assists) led the Sixers in the loss. Trae Young now sits nine 3PT FG away from passing Mookie Blaylock for most 3PT FGs in franchise history.
